--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Name   : gnu_grep
Type   : ansible role
Group  : sys-apps

Authors: liv community
License: Simplified BSD License

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages gnu_grep.

The GNU versions of commonly used grep utilities. Grep searches through textual
input for lines which contain a match to a specified pattern and then prints the
matching lines. GNU's grep utilities include grep, egrep and fgrep.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: gnu_grep
    vars:
      gnu_grep_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: gnu_grep
    vars:
      gnu_grep_state: 'remove'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: gnu_grep
    vars:
      gnu_grep_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  gnu_grep_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove  : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

